      <akn:section eId="sec_34_2401_25a">
        <akn:num>34-2401.25a</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Permitting authority to install meters.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_34-2401_25a_1">
      <akn:num>(1)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The District of Columbia Water and Sewer Authority shall install such a meter or meters (and incidental vaults, valves, piping and recording devices, and such other equipment as the Authority deems necessary) not later than 60 days after the expiration of such period; and</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_34-2401_25a_2">
      <akn:num>(2)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The department, independent establishment, or agency shall pay the Authority promptly (but in no case later than 30 days after the Authority submits a bill) for the costs incurred in installing the meter and equipment.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
